---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import srcImage from "../../assets/best-trout-fishing-spots-medford-oregon.png";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import MyH1 from "../../components/MyH1.astro";
import Bests from "../../components/Bests.astro";
---
<Layout 
title="Best trout fishing spots near Medford, Oregon"
description="Comprehensive guide to the best trout fishing hotspots – with seasonal tips, gear suggestions, and local insights."
url="https://medford.oregonfishingforum.com/trout/best-spots/"
type="article"
site_name="Medford Fishing"
ogimage={srcImage.src}
footer_location="trout-best-spots"
>
    <div class="text-center">
			<MyH1 text="Best trout fishing spots near Medford, Oregon" />
			<p class="mb-4">Comprehensive guide to the best trout fishing hotspots – with seasonal tips, gear suggestions, and local insights.</p>

			<Image
				src={srcImage}
				alt="Best trout fishing spots near Medford, Oregon"
                width={1344}
                height={768}
				loading={"eager"}
				fetchpriority={"high"}
                layout='constrained'
                class="rounded-xl shadow mx-auto"
				/>
				<br>
    </div>

<h3>
    <strong>1. Upper Rogue River (Above Lost Creek Lake)</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Species:</strong> Wild rainbow and cutthroat trout
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Access:</strong> Bank access at Cole Rivers Hatchery, Casey State Recreation Site, TouVelle, Rogue Elk, Dodge Bridge and more along Highway 62
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Notes:</strong> Weekly summer stockings and excellent fly/loring opportunities for trout and steelhead&nbsp;
    </li>
</ul>
<h3>
    <strong>2. Fish Lake</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Species:</strong> Stocked rainbow and brook trout, occasional trophy-sized wild browns
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Access:</strong> Resort area with boat rentals and accessible bank fishing
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Season:</strong> Fishable year-round; stocked April–July with trophy plantings in September
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    &nbsp;
</p>
<h3>
    <strong>3. Lost Creek Lake (Reservoir)</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Species:</strong> Hatchery rainbows, landlocked Chinook, cutthroat, browns
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Access:</strong> Multiple boat ramps and extensive shoreline in Joseph H. Stewart State Park
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Tips:</strong> Fish deeper during warm summer months; trolling spoons and flashers recommended
    </li>
</ul>
<h3>
    <strong>4. Howard Prairie &amp; Hyatt Lakes</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Species:</strong> Stocked rainbow trout, plus warmwater species 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Access:</strong> Boat and easy bank access, with ADA facilities available 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Notes:</strong> Fishing peaks after spring and fall stocking events&nbsp;
    </li>
</ul>
<h3>
    <strong>5. Emigrant Lake</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Species:</strong> Stocked rainbow trout, plus bass and other warmwater species
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Access:</strong> Boat ramps on western side and near Songer Wayside; bank access throughout county park
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Family-friendly:</strong> Amenities like restrooms and camping make it ideal for groups
    </li>
</ul>
<h3>
    <strong>6. Applegate Lake</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Species:</strong> Rainbows, kokanee, smallmouth bass 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Access:</strong> Shore fishing around dam and creek arms; best deeper areas accessed by boat 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Tips:</strong> Troll deep lures early in the season for kokanee and deep trout&nbsp;
    </li>
</ul>

<h2>
    Urban &amp; Easy-Access Ponds
</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Bear Creek Greenway &amp; Medford Pond System</strong> – Seasonal trout and steelhead in cooler months; ideal for casual fishing 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Reinhart Pond (Grants Pass)</strong> – Stocked with trout, bass, bluegill; small ponds great for beginners
    </li>
</ul>
<h2>
    Seasonal Highlights
</h2>
<figure class="table">
    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>
                    <strong>Time of Year</strong>
                </th>
                <th>
                    <strong>Best Spots &amp; Activity</strong>
                </th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>
                    <strong>Spring (Mar–May)</strong>
                </td>
                <td>
                    Fish lake stockings (Howard, Hyatt, Fish Lake), Rogue above Lost Creek for trout
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>
                    <strong>Summer (Jun–Aug)</strong>
                </td>
                <td>
                    Lost Creek and Emigrant lakes deeper trolling, Rogue for wild trout
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>
                    <strong>Fall (Sept–Oct)</strong>
                </td>
                <td>
                    Fish Lake trophy goals, lake stocking resumes, Rogue artificial-fly season
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>
                    <strong>Winter (Nov–Feb)</strong>
                </td>
                <td>
                    Stocked ponds, urban streams like Bear Creek, Fish Lake with Sno-Park pass
                </td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
</figure>
<h2>
    Pro Tips for Trout Fishing Near Medford
</h2>
<ol>
    <li>
        <strong>Match gear to conditions</strong>: Spinners, PowerBait, or small spoons work best across most waters.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Fish after stocking</strong>: Check the ODFW trout stocking schedule before heading out
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Try multiple locations</strong>: Robertson Bridge, Bear Creek, and Emigrant offer productive urban options.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Boat gives advantage</strong>: For reservoirs, boat or kayak access reaches tougher spots 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Respect regulations</strong>: Daily bag limits (5 trout in lakes/ponds, 2 in rivers) and seasonal closures apply .
    </li>
</ol>

<Bests bestFor="trout" />
</Layout>